SIMPLE: flick
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flick
<hw>Flick</hw> <pr>(fl⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Flicked</conjf> <pr>(fl⟦icr⟧kt)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Flicking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
<ets>Flicker</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To whip lightly or with a
quick jerk; to flap; <as>as, to <ex>flick</ex> a horse; to
<ex>flick</ex> the dirt from boots.</as></def>
<rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To throw, snap, or toss with a jerk; to flirt;
<as>as, to <ex>flick</ex> a whiplash</as>.</def></p>

<p><q>Rude boys were <qex>flicking</qex> butter pats across chaos.</q>
<rj><qau>Kipling.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flick</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Flick
<hw>Flick</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A flitch; <as>as, a <ex>flick</ex> of
bacon</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flick</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Flick
<hw>Flick</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Flick</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A light quick stroke or blow, esp. with
something pliant; a flirt; also, the sound made by such a
blow.</def></p>

<p><q>She actually took the whip out of his hand and gave a
<qex>flick</qex> to the pony.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs. Humphry
Ward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A motion picture; <as>as, I went to see a
<ex>flick</ex> on Friday</as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flicker</ent>⟦br⟧
